JOHANNESBURG - The Black Business Council (BBC) is probing the disappearance of a R5-million donation from its coffers. The lobby group received the money from the Airports Company South Africa (Acsa). The BBC has asked audit firm, Sizwe Ntsaluba Gobodo, to look into the matter. READ:Â Black Business Council looking to the East for business opportunities The investigation will consider why the funds never made it to the council's bank account. The organisation said it will now create a new strategy to raise funds. Acsa said it is awaiting the report on how the funds were used. eNCA